<subSubSection type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus Myers 1932</taxonomicName>
: 159-162 (original description, type species: 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8DF8C2F2-A5F1-4548-BC19-AD4E00BDC5AB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus transilis Myers 1932:160" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="transilis">A. transilis Myers</taxonomicName>
, by original designation, based on single specimen). Hoedeman 1961: 89-91 (based on head scale patterns, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
put in separate subfamily from 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
). Weitzman and Wourms 1967: 89-100 (generic characters discussed, validity of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EF0F634C-4A82-4B33-86D6-31A498C4DB7C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Pterolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pterolebias Garman 1895:141" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pterolebias</taxonomicName>
is doubted). Vaz-Ferreira and Sierra de Soriano 1972: 38-40 (attempt to distinguish 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
based on neuromast and lateral pore patterns, caudal and pelvic-fin morphology). Thomerson 1979: (comments on generic name). Elder Jr. et al. 1991: (karyotypes, comments on generic names). Costa 1990: (based primarily on osteological and meristic characters, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
placed into synonymy of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
). Costa 1998: (
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
revalidated but without explanation). Huber 1999: (morphometric relationships to other rivulin genera). Hrbek and Larson 1999: (phylogeny based on mitochondrial DNA data). Murphy et al. 1999: (phylogeny based on mitochondrial DNA data).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="12">
Diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
are Neotropical, northern South American, annual rivulid fishes that are distinguished from all new world rivulids except 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
in having at least the basal 45% of the caudal fin scaled. They differ from the closely related genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
(see Fig. 4) in having: more dorsal rays, usually 14 or more (range 12-18) vs. 13 or fewer (range 9-14); a longer dorsal fin base, more than 16% SL (12-25%) vs. less than 16% (10-18%); more lateral scales, usually 32 or more (28-38) vs. 32 or fewer (27-33); and more transverse scales, usually 11 or more (9-16) vs. usually 10 or less (8-11). Many males of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevis">R. brevis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculipinnis">R. maculipinnis</taxonomicName>
have a dark blotch around white spots on the dorsal fin, a pattern never seen in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
, which never has white spots on the dorsal fin of males. The anal and genital papillae are usually heavily pigmented in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
but only lightly pigmented or unpigmented in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
and other new world rivulids from northern South America.
</paragraph>
